# Fix Gallery UI, Storage Rules, and Seed Pipelines

This plan addresses the three primary issues reported:
1. Gallery images appearing outside their box and missing `.ui-gallery` semantic CSS.
2. The `storage/unauthorized` exception when trying to upload to `public/logos` during onboarding.
3. The lack of automatic pipeline seeding when the local emulator is started from scratch.

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Refactor [Gallery.tsx](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/components/ui/Gallery.tsx) and Add Semantic CSS

#### [MODIFY] src/app/globals.css
- Add new semantic classes for the Gallery component to adhere to the project's styling pattern.
- New classes to add:
  - `.ui-gallery`: Wrapper for the Gallery component.
  - `.ui-gallery-grid`: Responsive grid container for items.
  - `.ui-gallery-dropzone`: The bordered dashed box for drag-and-drop.
  - `.ui-gallery-item`: Individual image preview wrapper.
  - `.ui-gallery-overlay`: The hover action overlay.

#### [MODIFY] src/components/ui/Gallery.tsx
- Restructure the UI rendering: instead of rendering the `dropzone` above a separate `grid` containing the images, unify them into a single `grid` block. The `dropzone` will simply behave as the final element (or first element) "cell" in the grid.
- Apply the newly created semantic `.ui-gallery-*` classes replacing the raw inline Tailwind strings.

### 2. Fix Storage Error during Onboarding
The Firebase Storage rules currently state:
```javascript
  match /public/{allPaths=**} {
    allow read: if true;
    allow write: if isAuthenticated();
  }
```
If this is still throwing `storage/unauthorized` for `public/logos`, it's typically an emulator synchronization issue over `request.auth` token propagation when using a raw client configuration without App Check token debug bypass, or because the path was structured differently string-wise.

#### [MODIFY] src/components/forms/OrganizationOnboarding.tsx
- Explicitly set `path="public/logos"` (already currently set, but to be confirmed).
- We will add extra debugging logs to [Gallery.tsx](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/components/ui/Gallery.tsx) upload hooks specifically to check Authentication state if the emulator still rejects it. 

### 3. Automatic Seeding for Pipelines & AI Skills

#### [NEW] scripts/seedLocalPipelines.mjs
Create a Node script that leverages the `firebase-admin` pattern seen in [seedLocalAdmin.mjs](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/scripts/seedLocalAdmin.mjs) to automatically recreate fundamental pipelines into the local Firestore environment if they don't exist.
- This script will contain hardcoded configurations for ALL 5 existing pipelines (as a code backup).
- It will safely replace the old `auth-onboarding` trigger with the new `organization-onboarding`.

#### [NEW] scripts/seedLocalAISkills.mjs
Create the corresponding script to seed AI skills as code, similarly acting as a code backup.

#### [MODIFY] scripts/offline.mjs
- Integrate the execution of `node scripts/seedLocalPipelines.mjs` and `node scripts/seedLocalAISkills.mjs` into the startup routine alongside [seedLocalAdmin.mjs](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/scripts/seedLocalAdmin.mjs) to guarantee these resources are seeded even without `sync:local`.

